          <mxGeometry height="60" width="290" x="1010" y="223" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="spiaGc8N6B3giQx-SNpL-14" parent="1" style="rounded=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fillColor=#dae8fc;strokeColor=#6c8ebf;" value="" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="60" width="290" x="1010" y="283" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="spiaGc8N6B3giQx-SNpL-15" parent="1" style="rounded=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fillColor=#dae8fc;strokeColor=#6c8ebf;" value="" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="60" width="290" x="1010" y="343" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="spiaGc8N6B3giQx-SNpL-16" parent="1" style="rounded=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fillColor=#dae8fc;strokeColor=#6c8ebf;" value="" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="47" width="290" x="1010" y="403" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="spiaGc8N6B3giQx-SNpL-17" parent="1" style="text;html=1;whiteSpace=wrap;overflow=hidden;rounded=0;" value="&lt;h1 style=&quot;margin-top: 0px;&quot;&gt;User Story&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;p&gt;1. User Opens the Application.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;2. User Clicks &#39;Select SigMF Metadata File&#39; button - File Dialog appears.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;3. User Select a .sigmf-meta file. (NOTE: check user input!!!)&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;4. Backend is cleared re-initialized with SigMF dataset; Dataset name is updated; Spectrogram View is cleared &amp;amp; initial view is populated.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;5. User scrolls around flickable - frontend triggers loading from backend.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;6. Back to 2 or quit app.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="460" width="260" x="1440" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="spiaGc8N6B3giQx-SNpL-18" parent="1" style="rounded=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;" value="Dataset Name" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="20" width="150" x="1080" y="100" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="spiaGc8N6B3giQx-SNpL-19" parent="1" style="text;html=1;whiteSpace=wrap;overflow=hidden;rounded=0;" value="&lt;h1 style=&quot;margin-top: 0px;&quot;&gt;Frontend-Backend Data Passing&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;p&gt;Some data needs to be passed from Frontend to Backend:&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;Spectrogram (Frontend):&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;chunkWidth -&amp;nbsp;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;width of a single spectrogram chunk.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;chunkHeight&lt;/b&gt; - the height of a single spectrogram chunk.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;totalHeight - &lt;/b&gt;the total height of the spectrogram (dependent on the size of the dataset).&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;div&gt;Steps:&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;1. Spectrogram view is initialized with hard-coded &lt;b&gt;chunkWidth&lt;/b&gt;, &lt;b&gt;chunkHeight &lt;/b&gt;pulled from the backend. &lt;b&gt;totalHeight&lt;/b&gt; is zero (no content).&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;---User selects dataset.---&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;3. &lt;b&gt;totalHeight&lt;/b&gt; is calculated using the &lt;b&gt;sampleCount&lt;/b&gt; in the dataset and the &lt;b&gt;chunkWidth&lt;/b&gt;. &lt;u&gt;totalHeight = sampleCount / chunkWidth?&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;4. Dataset configures spectrogram parameters:&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;white-space: pre;&quot;&gt;&#x9;&lt;/span&gt;- fftSize&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;white-space: pre;&quot;&gt;&#x9;&lt;/span&gt;- window&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;white-space: pre;&quot;&gt;&#x9;&lt;/span&gt;- noverlap&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;white-space: pre;&quot;&gt;&#x9;&lt;/span&gt;- ...&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;5. Frontend is updated with newly calculated totalHeight and begins making requests for spectrogram Chunks.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;6. Backend receives requests for spectogram chunks, and begins generating them as QImages, then pushing back to the Frontend.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="430" width="425" x="942.5" y="760" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="spiaGc8N6B3giQx-SNpL-20" parent="1" style="text;html=1;whiteSpace=wrap;overflow=hidden;rounded=0;" value="&lt;h1 style=&quot;margin-top: 0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;Frontend States&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;h1 style=&quot;margin-top: 0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255)); font-size: 12px; font-weight: normal;&quot;&gt;There are a few valid states that we can be in.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;p&gt;* Blank Spectrogram (No Dataset selected) -&amp;gt; this is the initial state. No data is displayed.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;* Populated Spectrogram (A Dataset is selected) -&amp;gt; this happens once the proper information is communicated from the frontend to the backend &amp;amp; back on how data should be displayed.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;* Failed Spectrogram (A dataset fails to load/crashes at runtime) -&amp;gt; the program warns the user that something catastrophic went wrong and tells the user.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="220" width="520" x="910" y="500" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
