        <mxCell id="spiaGc8N6B3giQx-SNpL-50" parent="1" style="text;html=1;whiteSpace=wrap;strokeColor=none;fillColor=none;align=left;verticalAlign=top;rounded=0;" value="ChunkSpectrogramResponse&amp;nbsp;knows of SigMFBackend, and makes a call to the SigMFDataset with a yOffset to get a chunk of spectrogram.&lt;div&gt;(should check if SigMFDataset object exists, as it could possibly NOT exist... return nothing? something? if it doesn&#39;t.&lt;/div&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="121" width="250" x="250" y="690" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="spiaGc8N6B3giQx-SNpL-51" parent="1" style="text;html=1;whiteSpace=wrap;strokeColor=none;fillColor=none;align=left;verticalAlign=top;rounded=0;" value="SigMFDataset knows of SigMFDataFile (where it pulls the IQ from using the yOffset and the hardcoded chunkWidth and chunkHeight) and SpectrogramBuilder (which knows the default spectrogram parameters and can give IQ to build a spectrogram as a QImage) and returns the QImage to the callee." vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="118" width="250" y="24" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="BPabmzHj7sxv_MmH5qd7-9" parent="1" style="text;html=1;whiteSpace=wrap;overflow=hidden;rounded=0;" value="&lt;h1 style=&quot;margin-top: 0px;&quot;&gt;Spectrogram Builder&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;p&gt;The purpose of spectrogram Builder is to generate a spectrogram as a QImage from any given vector of IQ samples. It must be first configured with common Spectrogram parameters, such as sampleRate, nperseg, noverlap, and nfft.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;* The spectrogram builder need to be able to be configured with spectrogram related parameters.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;* The spectrogram builder needs to be able to generate a spectrogram given those parameters, and store them to a QImage.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;* The spectrogram builder needs to be able to return the frequency center of any bin given a bin index.&lt;/p&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="260" width="550" x="-840" y="660" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
      </root>
